Once I finished the 2nd season of my web series, I told myself I'd move to LA to further pursue my career with all of the knowledge and experience I gathered - which I did, and so far have succeeded.

Through the web series, I became part of the fledgling YouTube community where I got to meet a ton of people, like Meghan Tonjes. I went to various gatherings, such as NYC's 789, the first VidCon, and was even an invited guest to the first Playlist Live. Strange, fun times.

Wrote it. Directed it. Produced it. Edited it. All out of my own pocket. I can not be more thankful or humbled by the amazing actors, crew, and friends who sacrificed their time to help create this show with me.
